<HTMLTextAreaElementCols>
<summary>
The <strong><c>cols</c></strong> property of the <see cref="HTMLTextAreaElement"/> interface is a positive integer representing the visible width of the multi-line text control, in average character widths. It reflects the <c>&amp;lt;textarea&amp;gt;</c> element&amp;apos;s <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/textarea#cols"><c>cols</c></see> attribute.
</summary>
<remarks>
<para>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/textarea">textarea</see><br/>-<see cref="HTMLTextAreaElement.Rows"/><br/>-<see cref="HTMLTextAreaElement.Wrap"/><br/>-CSS <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/resize">resize</see> property<br/></para>
<para><seealso href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLTextAreaElement/cols"> <em>See also on MDN</em> </seealso></para>
</remarks>
<value>A positive integer. Defaults to <c>20</c>.</value>
</HTMLTextAreaElementCols>
